  "introduction": "The rapid proliferation of social media platforms has fundamentally altered the landscape of adolescent development, creating a complex environment where digital interactions often supersede face-to-face connections. Researchers have observed that the constant stream of curated images and instant feedback loops can significantly distort self-perception and emotional regulation during these critical formative years. As teenagers increasingly spend hours scrolling through feeds, the psychological toll becomes evident, manifesting in heightened anxiety and depressive symptoms. Furthermore, the pressure to maintain a perfect online persona forces many young individuals to engage in behaviors that prioritize digital validation over genuine well-being. This shift in social dynamics raises serious questions about the long-term consequences of such pervasive connectivity, prompting experts to examine the multifaceted nature of this digital phenomenon with increasing urgency.",
